27 families and school personnel about the rights of children of military
28 families; and
29
30 WHEREAS, the Arkansas Council for Military Children works to resolve
31 education-related issues for children of military families in transition; and
32
33 WHEREAS, the members of the Arkansas Council for Military Children work
34 with public school districts, charter schools, private schools, and military
35 installations across the State of Arkansas to raise awareness of and increase
36 support for children of military families; and
